        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 8:07PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 807 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Fountain, or 20 miles south of Colorado Springs,
moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fountain, Security-Widefield, and Hanover.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
central, southeastern and east central Colorado.</instruction>
